1) Clone of repository

    git clone <repository_url>

2) Create branch

    git branch <branch_name>

3) Delete branch

    git branch -D <branch_name>

4) Switch to other branch

    git checkout <branch_name>

5) Add files to 

    git add <file_names_seperated_by_space>

6) Commit 

    git commit -am "<msg_for_commit>"

7) Remote branch files merge with local branch

    git pull origin <branch_name>

8) Push branch

    git push origin <branch_name>

9) Get remote branch to local

    git fetch origin <branch_name>

    git checkout <branch_name>

10) Stash commands (Temporary backup)

    git stash 

    git stash list

    git stash apply "stash@{stash_index}"

    git stash drop

11) Merge local branch in current branch

    git merge <other_branch_which_is_to_be_merged>


12) Diff Tool

    git difftool -d .       # compares current files with last commit id

    git difftool -d <branch_name>      # compares current file with specified branch name


13) Revert commit

    git revert <commit_id>



    